The paper discusses logic-based methods for specifying and solving complex configuration problems for software components, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions constraint and logic programming, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the use of description logics and satisfiability and its extensions suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB).
